        <time datetime="2006-05-20">20.05.2006, 00:00</time>
        <h1>
            <a href="/blog/2006/05/20/ObjectivelyProPollution.html.." rel="bookmark canonical">Objectively Pro-Pollution</a>
        </h1>
    </header>
    <a class="reference external image-reference" href="http://thinkprogress.org/2006/05/18/new-ads-funded-by-big-oil-portray-global-warming-science-as-smear-campaign-against-carbon-dioxide/"><img alt="New Ads Funded by Big Oil Portray Global Warming Science as Smear Campaign Against Carbon Dioxide" class="right-float" src="http://thinkprogress.org/wp-content/uploads/2006/05/cei_ad.JPG"/></a>
<p>A front group for Big Oil is <a class="reference external" href="http://thinkprogress.org/2006/05/18/new-ads-funded-by-big-oil-portray-global-warming-science-as-smear-campaign-against-carbon-dioxide/">putting out ads</a>
denying the reality of global warming, in a pre-emptive bid
to undermine Al Gore's new doc&shy;u&shy;men&shy;tary,
<a class="reference external" href="http://www.climatecrisis.net/">An In&shy;con&shy;ve&shy;nient Truth</a>.</p>
<blockquote>
The first ad portrays global warming science as a vicious smear campaign
against carbon dioxide. The ad, which despite ap&shy;pear&shy;ances is not an SNL
parody, helpfully reminds us that carbon dioxide is “essential to life”
because “we breath[e] it out.”</blockquote>
<p>&quot;An In&shy;con&shy;ve&shy;nient Truth&quot; opens in Seattle on <a class="reference external" href="http://www.climatecrisis.net/findatheater/">June 2nd, 2006</a>.</p>

